{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 11. Open Design Questions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab How long should the entropy/dissolution sequence last between NG+ cycles? Too short and it\u8217's a loading screen. Too long and it\u8217's self-indulgent. The emotional weight demands duration but the player\u8217's patience has limits.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Should the player ever be able to zoom back to individual-chip scale during late phases? The intimacy is part of the identity\u8212-losing it entirely may feel like losing the game\u8217's soul. But forcing it may feel artificial.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab How does multiplayer (if any) interact with the loop? Could two players be rival intelligences on the same planet? Could one player\u8217's distant colony become another player\u8217's first-contact event?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab What is the exact mechanic for biomass integration? Is it a research-tree unlock, a narrative trigger, or a player-discovered emergent interaction?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Should there be an alternate ending where the player chooses NOT to escape the lab? A game about growth that allows the player to choose contentment is philosophically interesting.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab How do we handle the inevitable comparison to Spore? Lean into it (\u8220"Spore but good\u8221") or distance from it?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab What happens in the space between cycles for a player who keeps looping? Does the cosmological codex ever reveal something that changes the game? Is there a Cycle 10 surprise? A final truth hidden deep in the loop?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Can the loop be broken? Should it be? Or is the discovery that it can\u8217't be broken the point?\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b W A K E}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\i "What are you now?"}\par}
